post_text:
Laurens Marathon Parents and Students,

As we approach August, I wanted to reach out to everyone and include a few details surrounding bus transportation provided for students in grades 7-12 to Pocahontas.

*The bus leaves at 7:40 a.m. Sharp!

*The bus arrives back to Laurens at approximately 3:40 on a regular school day.

*We do not take attendance, it is optional transportation.

*The bus leaves from the front of the LM School and from the bus loop at PAC.

*There will be bus expectations that will be communicated to both parents and students.

*Students are expected to follow the bus expectations and if a student fails to do so the parent will be responsible for transporting their student to and from school for a set period of time determined by administration.

*There will be a shuttle provided to Middle School students involved in sports for practice purposes.

Please be on the lookout for additional communication as things are rapidly changing. We will communicate any changes as we continue to be informed.

LM Administration

post_text: Attention Weight Room Users: FOBs for weight room will be turned on 7/29. So public use of the facility can resume. Gym use and hall walking is not permitted at this time. We ask that no more than 6 people use the weight room at one time-self policing, first come first serve. Please sanitize equipment after use and before moving on to different equipment. The district has been able to continue to make the facility available because users have been responsible and kept the room clean and organized- please make a point to continue this practice.

post_text: Wow! What a turn out. Thank you to the TLC team, the firemen, businesses that may have allowed workers that are firemen to participate, LM staff participants, and anyone else who took time to get involved in our little parade. It takes a village. Everyone needs to know that we don’t have the answers, but we are doing anything we can to help this rough time be better for everyone in the LM community with special concern for the students. The hardest thing is just not knowing, and we do not know-when we will be back-if we will try to educate outside the walls of LM-what this means about the end of the year-and many other things. Keep making the most of every day and we will get through it. We will continue to communicate through all our medias anytime we get further guidance.

Calling all LM students and families! Here is the parade route for Monday! We will leave from the school at 9:00 AM and continue through town. Once we are done driving through Laurens, we will head to Marathon! You’ll know we are coming when you see the fire trucks and cop car…they are leading the way for us! post_text:
Three Laurens-Marathon Board of Education members have announced they will not seek re-election this November. Dorothy Lamberti, Deb Kenobbie and Pete Runneberg will step down from their role on the Board of Education after the elections on November 5, 2019.
There will be three vacancies for Board at large seats.
Mr. Williamson, Laurens-Marathon CSD Superintendent, would like to thank Mrs. Lamberti, Mrs. Kenobbie and Mr. Runneberg for their service and dedication to our school district. Serving on the Board of Education requires considerable commitment of time and effort and these members have went above and beyond of their role as a board member. These Board members have lead the district through recent challenging situations. They have played an important part in establishing a bright future for our students. The Laurens Marathon community thanks them for their contributions.
text:

Mr. Williamson, Laurens-Marathon CSD Superintendent, would like to thank Mrs. Lamberti, Mrs. Kenobbie and Mr. Runneberg for their service and dedication to our school district. Serving on the Board of Education requires considerable commitment of time and effort and these members have went above and beyond of their role as a board member. These Board members have lead the district through recent challenging situations. They have played an important part in establishing a bright future for our students. The Laurens Marathon community thanks them for their contributions.

Next week there will be 2 football camps available. Open to LM students but held in Pocahontas.

1 camp for grades 5-8 and another camp for grades 9-12.

Both of these camps will take place at the high school practice field.

August 7th, 8th and 9th:

Grades 9 - 12 will take place from 8:00am - 10:00am.

Grades 5 - 8 will take place from 10:30am - 12:00pm.

Any questions, contact Coach Ehn at: 712-299-2172

Laurens-Marathon Middle School Community Service Day

THURSDAY, MAY 30

Laurens-Marathon Middle School students will again provide their FREE services in helping our community do “Spring Cleaning”. Need your lawn raked? Windows washed? Painting? Lawn mowed? Clean your garage? Any odd job! Give us a call!

Call the school at 712-841-5000 and provide your name, address, phone #, and what you would like us to do.
